When clicking on a line in a callback trace in the console pane that has a 
reference to an package level class that does not have a file on it's own I get 
the message that says it cannot find the source. 

Eclipse Version 3.1M4 

Example trace: 
--------------- 
Exception in thread "main" java.lang.RuntimeException: Opps 
	at scratch.X.m(NF.java:12) 
	at scratch.NF.main(NF.java:6) 

Clicking on the first line in trace gives "Cannot find source for scratch.X". 

Example source: 
--------------- 
package scratch; 

public class NF { 

  public static void main(String[] args) { 
    X.m(); 
  } 
} 

class X { 
  static void m() { 
    throw new RuntimeException("Opps");       
  } 
}
